Now that headline,

48:50.127 --> 48:51.361
I'd toiler for.

48:52.429 --> 48:53.429
- T.

48:54.631 --> 48:56.366
Joseph T. Herrington.

48:57.467 --> 48:59.045
Not Joseph Herrington
the plumber,

48:59.069 --> 49:00.880
Joseph Herrington
sanitary worker,

49:00.904 --> 49:03.883
Joseph T Herrington, litigator,

49:03.907 --> 49:05.685
that's something you
seem to forget.

49:05.709 --> 49:08.821
There will be no settlement.

49:08.845 --> 49:10.456
- Very well.

49:10.480 --> 49:12.215
Joseph Herrington. T.

49:15.419 --> 49:17.563
- With your client and his
lawyer, I would expect this

49:17.587 --> 49:21.034
to be the shortest
deliberation in history.

49:21.058 --> 49:22.058
We're done.

49:37.941 --> 49:39.552
- $5,000.

49:39.576 --> 49:40.576
One hand.

51:29.186 --> 51:33.099
I wasn't sure if I
should run or slug you.

51:33.123 --> 51:35.163
- You said that you wanted
to talk so I hope you got

51:35.187 --> 51:36.235
some good news for me.

51:36.259 --> 51:37.870
- You should've made
an appointment.

51:37.894 --> 51:39.806
My life doesn't revolve
around this case.

51:39.830 --> 51:43.309
- I never seen another soul
anywhere near this office.

51:43.333 --> 51:45.378
Hopefully we'll just be
back to normal living,

51:45.402 --> 51:47.042
you know as soon as we
get the settlement.

51:47.066 --> 51:48.667
Thank God for that.

51:52.409 --> 51:55.254
- You lost your job,
your house, your team,

51:55.278 --> 51:56.422
your record,

51:56.446 --> 51:58.115
still you thank God.

52:01.084 --> 52:03.587
You lost your job for praying.

52:04.454 --> 52:08.201
If prayer was so powerful,
wouldn't you still be working?

52:08.225 --> 52:09.335
- What am I supposed to do?

52:09.359 --> 52:11.971
Just be faithful when I am

52:11.995 --> 52:13.830
rolling in the riches,

52:14.865 --> 52:15.865
balling,

52:16.833 --> 52:17.833
on top.

52:19.903 --> 52:21.805
- They're not settling.

52:27.277 --> 52:29.212
- They're not settling?

52:30.747 --> 52:32.649
- They're not settling.

52:33.884 --> 52:35.804
- That's funny because I
thought that you told me

52:35.828 --> 52:37.563
they called you

52:37.587 --> 52:41.167
and said that they
wanted to settle.

52:41.191 --> 52:42.735
- They called,

52:42.759 --> 52:44.203
but they snuck me.

52:44.227 --> 52:45.228
- Snuck you?

52:47.397 --> 52:50.910
Oh I see so they outsmarted
you is what you're saying.

52:50.934 --> 52:53.813
- Say it any way you want.

52:53.837 --> 52:56.339
But that's not the worst part.

52:57.741 --> 52:59.619
- That's not the worst part?

52:59.643 --> 53:02.054
What's the worst part?

53:02.078 --> 53:06.359
- No matter what happens,
just keep praying right?

53:06.383 --> 53:09.061
- Why don't you go ahead and
tell me the worst part?

53:09.085 --> 53:10.085
- Look,

53:11.154 --> 53:12.798
you see that stack of
motions they filed.

53:12.822 --> 53:16.593
That's 50 grand in fees
sitting on that desk.

53:18.828 --> 53:21.407
- Where's your stack of motions?

53:21.431 --> 53:22.875
- You didn't pay me 50 grand.

53:22.899 --> 53:26.403
- Well what is five
grand stack look like?

53:31.141 --> 53:32.542
That's really it?

53:33.510 --> 53:35.054
That's really it?

53:35.078 --> 53:36.756
- And there's more.

53:36.780 --> 53:37.780
- More?

53:38.682 --> 53:40.726
Oh there's more?

53:40.750 --> 53:41.750
- More.

53:44.688 --> 53:46.790
- There's even more. Wow.

53:57.567 --> 53:59.078
- You should've told me.

53:59.102 --> 54:01.771
- This is supposed to be sealed.

54:06.343 --> 54:08.120
Why are you handing me this?

54:08.144 --> 54:10.723
This is sealed.

54:10.747 --> 54:11.891
This is sealed record.

54:11.915 --> 54:13.826
- If that gets in.

54:13.850 --> 54:15.061
You can't win.

54:15.085 --> 54:16.796
- What do you mean
if it gets in?

54:16.820 --> 54:19.060
It's not supposed to be in,
it's not supposed to be here,

54:19.084 --> 54:21.534
you're not supposed, no one is
ever supposed to be able to

54:21.558 --> 54:22.868
look at this.

54:22.892 --> 54:25.829
Because it's supposed
to be sealed.

54:27.897 --> 54:30.409
We're dropping this lawsuit
right now, do you understand?

54:30.433 --> 54:31.277
- Drop it?

54:31.301 --> 54:32.211
- Yeah. I can't go to trial

54:32.235 --> 54:33.479
with a lawyer... - They have it!

54:33.503 --> 54:35.263
- Who can't keep something
that was sealed as

54:35.287 --> 54:38.651
a minor record.
- Their money unsealed it.

54:38.675 --> 54:40.515
- There's no way this
should be here right now,

54:40.539 --> 54:41.587
do you understand?

54:41.611 --> 54:43.122
There's no way.

54:43.146 --> 54:44.557
- So you just want to drop it?

54:44.581 --> 54:45.691
- Yeah, that's right.

54:45.715 --> 54:47.326
- All my time.

54:47.350 --> 54:49.261
The kids are important.

54:49.285 --> 54:51.030
Et cetera and so forth.

54:51.054 --> 54:53.099
You know I don't get you, swami.

54:53.123 --> 54:54.457
I don't get you.

54:56.292 --> 54:58.471
One minute you're all about
prayer and the next minute

54:58.495 --> 55:00.172
you're ready to quit.

55:00.196 --> 55:02.274
- Ready to quit?

55:02.298 --> 55:04.810
- I'm not quitting anything,
I'm getting out of suicide

55:04.834 --> 55:06.846
right now, that's
what I'm doing.

55:06.870 --> 55:09.015
I lost my job, I lost my
bike, I lost my house,

55:09.039 --> 55:11.384
I lost my living, I
lost everything.

55:11.408 --> 55:13.048
And all I keep... I'm
waiting for answers,

55:13.072 --> 55:15.054
all I keep getting is you,
sitting here telling me

55:15.078 --> 55:16.288
it gets worse.

55:16.312 --> 55:19.191
Oh they outsmarted me. Oh.

55:19.215 --> 55:21.427
You're sealed record from
when you were 10 years old

55:21.451 --> 55:25.097
is now public because they
have money and we don't.

55:25.121 --> 55:26.356
- That's right.

55:28.024 --> 55:31.904
I tell you this so you know
what we're up against.

55:31.928 --> 55:35.532
I tell you this so that
you can understand,

55:36.366 --> 55:38.535
they're playing for keeps.

55:39.969 --> 55:40.969
You get it?

55:43.173 --> 55:44.173
You get it?

55:44.974 --> 55:46.810
And all you got is me.

55:49.079 --> 55:50.079
Hm, me.

55:51.247 --> 55:53.526
The only person crazy
enough or desperate enough

55:53.550 --> 55:55.561
to take your case.

55:55.585 --> 55:58.197
The only person who's willing
to stick their neck out

55:58.221 --> 55:59.031
for you.

55:59.055 --> 56:00.890
The only person who...

56:05.195 --> 56:07.173
You can't quit.

56:07.197 --> 56:08.365
We can't quit.

56:09.666 --> 56:11.911
I didn't tell you this to quit.

56:11.935 --> 56:14.037
I told you this to fight!

56:18.975 --> 56:21.454
Now you asked me
something the other day.

56:21.478 --> 56:23.255
You asked me did I
want to make history,

56:23.279 --> 56:26.158
well I'm telling you now.

56:26.182 --> 56:27.784
Let's make history.

56:28.752 --> 56:32.522
- What are we gonna do
about this, Mr. Brown?

57:18.668 --> 57:20.336
- Mr. Brown?

57:33.450 --> 57:35.351
- Ladies and gentlemen,

57:36.319 --> 57:40.800
our legal system trust the
community to enforce the law.

57:40.824 --> 57:43.326
Today, you are that community,

57:44.627 --> 57:47.106
your job is important.

57:47.130 --> 57:48.965
And relatively simple.

57:49.899 --> 57:54.747
You have to decide if Aiden
Paul violated a rule,

57:54.771 --> 57:58.708
and whether any violation
deserved termination.

58:00.577 --> 58:01.577
Now,

58:02.912 --> 58:06.325
they will tell you that Mr.
Paul was terminated for

58:06.349 --> 58:08.184
praying with a player,

58:09.385 --> 58:14.066
and that that prayer constituted
a violation of policy,

58:14.090 --> 58:15.835
and for that,

58:15.859 --> 58:17.760
termination was proper.

58:18.995 --> 58:21.564
And then you'll hear the truth.

58:26.102 --> 58:27.203
The truth is,

58:28.504 --> 58:31.650
that Mr. Paul threatened
to report the school's

58:31.674 --> 58:34.854
principal's violations
to the Board,

58:34.878 --> 58:38.114
and later, that same
day, he was fired.

58:46.389 --> 58:49.792
Those are the facts
ladies and gentlemen.

58:51.394 --> 58:52.394
At the end,

59:05.642 --> 59:06.642
actually,

59:08.811 --> 59:10.723
the reason we're here

59:10.747 --> 59:11.747
is prayer.

59:15.451 --> 59:17.186
And where you believe

59:18.121 --> 59:20.189
it's greatest value lies.

59:23.426 --> 59:24.426
Thank you.

59:33.036 --> 59:34.246
- Oh.

59:34.270 --> 59:35.270
The truth.

59:37.240 --> 59:38.240
The truth.

59:40.243 --> 59:43.155
You know, when
someone tells you,

59:43.179 --> 59:47.326
they declare that they rely
on the truth all too often,

59:47.350 --> 59:49.352
in actuality, the truth,

59:50.453 --> 59:51.688
it evades them.

59:53.923 --> 59:56.502
Because they're so
blinded by their

59:56.526 --> 59:59.462
passionate stand
of their position.

01:00:01.464 --> 01:00:06.111
Now I have no doubt that Mr.
Brown believes his client's

01:00:06.135 --> 01:00:09.572
position carries the
shield of the truth.

01:00:12.041 --> 01:00:15.311
But reality is far
from that barometer.

01:00:16.279 --> 01:00:20.059
You see in 1962, our
Supreme Court held

01:00:20.083 --> 01:00:24.229
that teacher led prayer
is unconstitutional.

01:00:24.253 --> 01:00:26.999
I'm gonna say it again,
listen very carefully.

01:00:27.023 --> 01:00:30.860
The Supreme Court held
that teacher led prayer

01:00:34.230 --> 01:00:35.898
is unconstitutional.

01:00:39.035 --> 01:00:42.214
Opening up prayer in school
is akin to opening up.

01:00:42.238 --> 01:00:44.817
Pandora's box, why,
because we don't want

01:00:44.841 --> 01:00:48.487
our children indoctrinated
with whatever religion,

01:00:48.511 --> 01:00:52.091
whatever religion, just
happens to be popular

01:00:52.115 --> 01:00:52.925
at the moment.

01:00:52.949 --> 01:00:54.017
So we say no.

01:00:55.618 --> 01:00:58.731
You want to discuss those things,
you want to ask questions

01:00:58.755 --> 01:01:02.034
you do it inside your own home.

01:01:02.058 --> 01:01:04.894
The separation of
church and state

01:01:06.329 --> 01:01:07.830
is an enforceable,

01:01:09.399 --> 01:01:10.566
constitutional

01:01:11.467 --> 01:01:12.467
principle.

01:01:14.871 --> 01:01:18.708
Mr. Paul very simply,
violated that principle,

01:01:21.511 --> 01:01:22.779
and the school,

01:01:24.313 --> 01:01:27.216
they terminated him
for doing such.

01:01:30.453 --> 01:01:35.134
That termination, you know
what that termination does?

01:01:35.158 --> 01:01:38.470
It protects our children
from the undue influence of

01:01:38.494 --> 01:01:41.840
people who happen to be popular.

01:01:41.864 --> 01:01:44.943
People that our children
look up to like Mr. Paul

01:01:44.967 --> 01:01:47.303
who will do anything to win.

01:01:52.475 --> 01:01:53.475
Influence.

01:01:54.711 --> 01:01:57.547
People who influence
our children.

01:02:01.184 --> 01:02:05.354
Ladies and gentlemen of the
jury, with that verdict.

01:02:07.490 --> 01:02:09.935
I want you to inform
the plaintiff,

01:02:09.959 --> 01:02:13.572
I want you to inform Mr.
Paul that we as a community

01:02:13.596 --> 01:02:16.332
we respect and we
uphold the law.

01:02:21.170 --> 01:02:24.006
No matter how many
athletic events

01:02:28.544 --> 01:02:30.613
you may coach to victory.

01:02:32.048 --> 01:02:33.048
We respect,

01:02:38.354 --> 01:02:40.189
and we uphold the law.

01:02:47.430 --> 01:02:48.430
Thank you.

01:03:02.411 --> 01:03:03.722
- Your Honor,

01:03:03.746 --> 01:03:07.183
plaintiff calls Kurt
Rogers to the stand.

01:03:34.704 --> 01:03:36.744
- It has been brought to the
court's attention that.

01:03:36.768 --> 01:03:39.625
Mr. Kurt Rodgers was never
properly served a subpoena

01:03:39.649 --> 01:03:42.194
to testify in court today.

01:03:42.218 --> 01:03:45.664
- Judge I was informed by the
witness that he would testify

01:03:45.688 --> 01:03:47.065
today,

01:03:47.089 --> 01:03:50.569
but I would move to admit
his deposition testimony.

01:03:50.593 --> 01:03:53.038
- Your Honor we object to the
admission of this deposition,

01:03:53.062 --> 01:03:55.240
we were not informed of
the deposition because.

01:03:55.264 --> 01:03:58.477
Mr. Brown deprived the
defense the opportunity to

01:03:58.501 --> 01:04:01.446
cross examine the witness, the
deposition is inadmissible

01:04:01.470 --> 01:04:03.372
hearsay under rule 801.

01:04:04.507 --> 01:04:05.918
- Mr. Brown?

01:04:05.942 --> 01:04:08.687
- I anticipated the witness
would be here to testify

01:04:08.711 --> 01:04:09.711
your Honor.

01:04:11.647 --> 01:04:13.225
- Not good enough.

01:04:13.249 --> 01:04:15.289
If the defense did not have
the opportunity to cross

01:04:15.313 --> 01:04:17.696
examine the witness,
the testimony,

01:04:17.720 --> 01:04:19.388
it's not admissible.

01:04:28.397 --> 01:04:30.976
- Your Honor, these witnesses
are inappropriate.

01:04:31.000 --> 01:04:33.412
The facts of this case
turn on whether Mr. Paul's

01:04:33.436 --> 01:04:36.715
termination was a violation
of school policy.

01:04:36.739 --> 01:04:38.819
- Your Honor, is counsel
gonna allow us to put on our

01:04:38.843 --> 01:04:41.920
case or continue these jack
in the box objections?

01:04:41.944 --> 01:04:46.115
- Is opposing counsel gonna
adhere to one single rule?

01:04:47.850 --> 01:04:50.195
- I agree with Mr. Herrington,
this case is not about.

01:04:50.219 --> 01:04:52.798
Mr. Paul's character, it
is only about whether he

01:04:52.822 --> 01:04:55.100
was terminated for
violating a rule,

01:04:55.124 --> 01:04:57.703
or for pretexual reason.

01:04:58.561 --> 01:04:59.629
Next witness.

01:05:04.467 --> 01:05:06.578
- Mr. Patterson, you
claimed that Coach Paul

01:05:06.602 --> 01:05:09.681
was terminated for
praying with a student?

01:05:09.705 --> 01:05:11.984
- That's correct, yes.

01:05:12.008 --> 01:05:15.487
- Isn't it true that on the
same day he was terminated,

01:05:15.511 --> 01:05:18.590
he informed you that he was
going to report you to the.

01:05:18.614 --> 01:05:22.527
Board for the misallocation of
funds assigned to the team?

01:05:22.551 --> 01:05:24.062
- Not in that way, no.

01:05:24.086 --> 01:05:25.530
- In what way then Mr.
Patterson?

01:05:25.554 --> 01:05:26.656
- I recall he

01:05:28.124 --> 01:05:30.135
mentioned some kind
of a complaint, but

01:05:30.159 --> 01:05:32.704
I don't recall him
threatening me to

01:05:32.728 --> 01:05:36.408
threatening to report
me to my superiors, no.

01:05:36.432 --> 01:05:39.211
- But if he was to do so on
the same day that he was

01:05:39.235 --> 01:05:40.579
terminated,

01:05:40.603 --> 01:05:43.048
it would look pretty bad
for you wouldn't it?

01:05:43.072 --> 01:05:45.284
- Yeah, if you say so.

01:05:45.308 --> 01:05:46.818
- Well did you?

01:05:46.842 --> 01:05:47.719
- Did I what?

01:05:47.743 --> 01:05:49.888
- Did you miss allocate funds?

01:05:49.912 --> 01:05:52.224
- Absolutely not, sir,
and I'm insulted.

01:05:52.248 --> 01:05:55.160
- Oh I'm so sorry
to insult you, sir.

01:05:55.184 --> 01:05:56.962
Do you need a moment
to gather yourself?

01:05:56.986 --> 01:05:57.796
- Objection your Honor.

01:05:57.820 --> 01:05:59.097
Argumentative.

01:05:59.121 --> 01:06:01.466
- Sustained. That statement
will be stricken.

01:06:01.490 --> 01:06:04.269
- Mr. Patterson praying
with a student

01:06:04.293 --> 01:06:06.038
is not a terminable
offense is it?

01:06:06.062 --> 01:06:07.063
- Yes it is.

01:06:09.298 --> 01:06:11.043
- According to your policies,

01:06:11.067 --> 01:06:15.147
conviction of a felony,
forgery, falsifying records,

01:06:15.171 --> 01:06:19.017
stealing, fighting, immoral
or indecent conduct,

01:06:19.041 --> 01:06:21.520
these are listed as
terminable offenses,

01:06:21.544 --> 01:06:25.590
and funny thing is, there's
no mention of prayer.

01:06:25.614 --> 01:06:28.126
- It's not specifically
stated, I'll give you that,

01:06:28.150 --> 01:06:31.153
it's assumed under
indecent conduct.

01:06:33.222 --> 01:06:34.666
- I'm sorry.

01:06:34.690 --> 01:06:37.703
Are you saying that your
school district categorizes

01:06:37.727 --> 01:06:39.962
prayer as indecent conduct?

01:06:41.163 --> 01:06:45.410
- Yes, but not in the way
you may think however.

01:06:45.434 --> 01:06:48.313
- Well pray tell
how do you do so?

01:06:48.337 --> 01:06:50.582
- Indecent defined as
not being the norm,

01:06:50.606 --> 01:06:53.676
not fitting, not
indecent as obscene.

01:06:54.543 --> 01:06:56.822
- The definition that
you're relying upon,

01:06:56.846 --> 01:07:00.292
this definition is written
in your policies?

01:07:00.316 --> 01:07:01.126
- No I don't think...

01:07:01.150 --> 01:07:02.385
- No it is not.

01:07:04.520 --> 01:07:08.133
You would agree, Mr. Patterson,
that being transgender

01:07:08.157 --> 01:07:09.534
is not the norm?

01:07:09.558 --> 01:07:11.136
- Honor, objection.

01:07:11.160 --> 01:07:12.938
- A little grace your Honor.

01:07:12.962 --> 01:07:14.206
- Very little.

01:07:14.230 --> 01:07:15.540
- Yes I would agree.

01:07:15.564 --> 01:07:18.410
- And there is a transgender
teacher working at your

01:07:18.434 --> 01:07:22.147
school, and a parent complained
because this teacher

01:07:22.171 --> 01:07:24.483
discussed it with a student.

01:07:24.507 --> 01:07:25.851
- I believe that's true, yes.

01:07:25.875 --> 01:07:28.487
- And according to
your definition,

01:07:28.511 --> 01:07:32.190
not being the norm
is indecent, right?

01:07:32.214 --> 01:07:34.493
- According to that
logic, I guess.

01:07:34.517 --> 01:07:37.028
- And that teacher
still teaches, yes?

01:07:37.052 --> 01:07:39.064
- Mr. Brown, precisely
what is your point?

01:07:39.088 --> 01:07:42.834
- My point is that you chose
to terminate Coach Paul

01:07:42.858 --> 01:07:46.004
for praying with a student
but you chose not to

01:07:46.028 --> 01:07:49.141
terminate a transgender
teacher who discussed

01:07:49.165 --> 01:07:52.168
their sexual identity
with students.

01:07:52.968 --> 01:07:54.136
Mr. Patterson.

01:07:56.539 --> 01:07:59.418
Tolerance and
understanding is a river,

01:07:59.442 --> 01:08:02.378
that flows both up
stream and down.

01:08:03.979 --> 01:08:04.980
Does it not?

01:08:26.001 --> 01:08:30.171
- Guard said it's about
that time, he's locking up.

01:08:33.876 --> 01:08:37.555
- My mentor was never allowed
to enter the room down there.

01:08:37.580 --> 01:08:40.292
He and everyone that looked
like him were forced to

01:08:40.316 --> 01:08:41.317
sit up here.

01:08:42.551 --> 01:08:44.487
Argue from the balcony.

01:08:46.255 --> 01:08:47.255
Separate.

01:08:50.759 --> 01:08:53.162
- Shackled by stupidity, huh?

01:08:55.163 --> 01:08:57.166
- Shackled by stupidity.

01:09:01.337 --> 01:09:03.072
- So I'm up tomorrow?

01:09:05.608 --> 01:09:07.542
- It comes down to you.

01:09:11.346 --> 01:09:14.091
- They can't bring up the
things about the past?

01:09:14.116 --> 01:09:16.285
- No I don't think so, but

